{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-make-order-status-visible-on-frontend-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How To Make Order Status Visible on Frontend in Magento 2","content":"\n<p><a href=\"https://business.adobe.com/products/magento/magento-commerce.html\">Magento 2</a> is a powerful e-commerce platform that provides a lot of flexibility and customization options for store owners. One such customization is the ability to show the order status on the frontend for customers to see, as well as the ability to select an <a href=\"/how-to-auto-select-shipping-method-in-magento-2/\">auto shipping method</a>. By default, Magento 2 does not display the order status on the frontend, but this information can be easily made visible with a few simple steps. In this blog, we&#8217;ll show you <strong><em>how to make the order status visible on the frontend in Magento 2</em></strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Make Order Status Visible on Frontend in Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Log in to the Magento 2 backend</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, log in to the Magento 2 backend using your admin credentials. Once logged in, navigate to the Stores menu and then to the Configuration section.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:546px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;691&#x27;%20width=&#x27;546&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\"