ne-image\":\"3\"}</script></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Change the option to &#8220;Yes&#8221;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To make the order status visible on the frontend, change the &#8220;Display Orders and Newsletter Statuses&#8221; option to &#8220;Yes.&#8221; Once you have made this change, click the &#8220;Save Config&#8221; button at the top of the page to save your changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 5: Verify the changes on the frontend</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To verify that the order status is now visible on the frontend, log out of the backend and navigate to your store&#8217;s frontend. Look for the My Account section and then click on the Order History link. In the Order History section, you should now see the order status for each order.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, making the order status visible on the frontend in Magento 2 is a simple process that can be accomplished in just a few steps. By following the steps outlined in this blog, you can provide your customers with easy access to their order status, which can improve their experience on your store and encourage repeat purchases.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-make-order-status-visible-on-frontend-in-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-a